choices.text:
what are the verb tenses?
Verb tense refers to how a verb is conjugated (or changed) depending on when it happened or will happen. There are three main types of verb tenses: past, present and future. Each type has different forms for each verb depending on whether the action occurred in the past, present or future. Additionally, there are also subcategories within these main categories such as perfect tense (past perfect, present perfect) and conditional tense (would have, could have).
